cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper presents an approach to check resource consumption contracts using an off-the-shelf static analyzer, which is a common topic in software engineering research. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a set of annotations to support resource usage specifications, which is related to programming language design and implementation. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses a proof-of-concept implementation using a specification language and a static verifier, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper proposes a specification language to express memory consumption and lifetime properties, which can be seen as a formal language. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses possible extensions of the approach to deal with non-linear expressions, which may involve cryptographic or security-related computations.
